Currently the nearby query ignores items that have no coordinate location set using P625 (https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P625) but link to an item using P276 (https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P276).

That means that items about events like this one: https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q42740247 or https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q18417962 are not listed as needing images. But people living close to venues might have images of those events.

I think we should add a query like this to our current nearby query:

```SPARQL
SELECT ?item ?itemLabel 
WHERE 
{
  ?item wdt:P276 [] .
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?item wdt:P18 ?any . }
  SERVICE wikibase:label { bd:serviceParam wikibase:language "en". }
}
LIMIT 100
```

